\section*{Discussion}
Our results show how the growth response to different season length changed across different species. With Acer showing the same growth response to all treatments indicates that this species may be little flexible, both in the short and long-term response to growing season length. With the treatment effects actually increasing for Betula, indicates that this species may utilize the earlier season (Warm spring) to increase its overall photosynthesis, store its byproducts as non-structural carbohydrate [-->introduce growth allocations through NSC in intro], but store them as reserve during year 1, to reinvest them in growht, only during the following year. 
